         <abstract>
            <p>A transform analogous to the discrete Fourier transform may be defined in a finite field, and may be calculated efficiently by the `fast Fourier transform' algorithm. The transform may be applied to the problem of calculating convolutions of long integer sequences by means of integer arithmetic.</p>
          </abstract>
